&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Psychologist, Band 8a &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and innovative Clinical Psychologist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit to join our expanding ASD service across Bromley, Bexley Greenwich for adults with Autism, who present with a range of comorbid mental health difficulties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for a current Band 8a psychologist looking to develop valued supervisory, clinical leadership and service development skills to progress their professional development. The post holder will be involved in completing diagnostic assessments for ASD and will be assisting with the delivery of the Transforming Care Programme to help prevent admissions for adults with a diagnosis of ASD. The post is advertised as a full time position, but a 30 hrs agreement can be considered as well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An highly motivated and experienced in ASD band 7 can also be considered for this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous experience of completing ASD assessments with adults, children or people with LD is required and training in either ADOS or DISCO, ADI-R, 3DI would be highly desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that Oxleas operates a probationary period, further information is available on request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Andrea Centonze - Principal Psychologist &amp; Clinical Lead - 02086 592151 or andrea.centonze1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
